title: For Sale:  Vintage Remington 541-S custom sporter
postcontent:
Remington 541 Custom Sporter. Vey nice rifle. This rifle is extremely accurate, which put it in the same league like Anschutz and Walther in silhouette competition. Discontinued in 1999 so no more to buy. It was topped with cheap CenterPoint 4-16x40 scope from Walmart but I took it off because it didn't look right with this type or rifle. 

The targets was shot at 50 distance no more no less (the scope has AO, so I'm positive to say that). Wind was about 5MPH (Weather Channel app in my Ipad said so). I shot it with variation of 22s but the gun liked Geco SV the best, almost five shot went through the same hole. The others were ok, but they all can be covered with a dime or penny. Pics ain't never lied. None of them were considered MATCH AMMO OR ANYTHING, but the results were very respectable for a 22lr cartridge. I think if I try with Match ammo like Wolf, Lapua or Eley, I can shoot a walnut off the tree (@ 75-100 yards, maybe?) with this gun. It's just an amazing rifle 

The winner's ammo list: (higher to lower)

1st: Geco Subsonic 1050 fps 
2nd: Fiocchi SV 1070 fps
3rd: Federal Gold Medal HV Match 1200 fps
4th: Blazer HV 1235 fps
5th: Norma USA Tac 22 1100 fps


 If you want this beauty, you better be quick to grab it. Shoots all 22s: S,L and LR. Engraved receiver. Adjustable trigger. And the trigger breaks like glass at  17oz. It can go even lower, but not recommended as for safety reason

If you can't meet in person to pick it up, I can ship it to your FFL for $40 insured. If you want my FFL to ship it, then add $20 more for their fee. Need more pictures? Just ask.

title: For Sale:  Blast from the Past - Beretta Mod. 950BS Jetfire in .25 ACP.
postcontent: Beretta Mod. 950BS in .25 ACP. - Private sale of an older classic Beretta in good condition. Made in Italy. When I called Beretta, they advised the gun's serial number predates their record keeping, and that based upon its features it had to have been manufactured sometime between 1950 and 1959. Bore is in excellent shape. I don't think it was shot much. Has a tip up barrel. Perfect gun for someone that is disabled, or has difficulty racking a slide (elderly, those with arthritis, small women etc...). You never rack the slide to shot this gun. You just drop a round in the tip up barrel, and once fired, it automatically cycles the next round. For a “mouse” gun, it has a large 8+1 capacity. Taurus also makes a small caliber tip barrel design, but has a much heavier trigger (due to being double action). The Beretta is only single action, (where the hammer resets due to the blowback from the fired cartridge, and not from pulling the trigger – The trigger only releases the hammer, which equals a light and smooth trigger). Very nice aged look. Nice, and small for concealed carry. Carry it with Hornady “magic” bullets, and it will be just as effective as a 40 caliber. I already have two (2) good shooting .25 acp caliber guns, and can't really justify keeping this one. Own a classic Beretta for only $155 (reduced). Private sale. Must be over 21, have a Florida D/L and be legally able to own a firearm. Sale will must take place at my office in Palm Harbor. Don't waste my time if you are not willing to sign a bill of sale, or won't allow me to make a copy of your Florida d/license. If you want to spend a little less, I am willing to keep the Beretta, and would sell one of my Ravens that is in like new condition (with box), with only about 150 rds through it for $130.00. I am selling a Glock 27 .40 caliber handgun in good working condition, only minor cosmetic flaws from normal wear and tear.  Great carry weapon in a powerful caliber.  If you are not used to shooting larger caliber handguns I do not recommend this gun.  It has never failed to go "bang" when I pull the trigger, as is expected with Glock firearms.  The only reason I am selling is to offset the purchase of a new Sig.

Included with purchase of Glock 27:
1) Original Glock hard case
2) 9 round magazines with pinky extensions
1) 9 round flush bottom magazine
1) IWB (Inside Waist Band) holster, kydex with clasp belt loops
2) Boxes of 20 hollow point defensive rounds

I also have plenty of target ammunition available (950+ rounds) that I would be willing to sell for $15/bx or ALL 950+ rounds for $250 which saves you $35 from box price (19 boxes plus a partial).  Currently you will not find it cheaper than $22/bx in stores.  Mix of factory loads from various manufacturers and Freedom Munitions re-manufactured rounds which are reloaded with factory presses and work just as well if not better than new loads from Remington, Federal, etc.  Glocks are not picky on ammo in the slightest.

Long story short:  You can have a Glock 27 in a case with 3 mags, a holster, 40 hollow points, and over 950 rounds of ammo for $675 plus transfer fee.  More than a fair deal any day of the week.

Price is non-negotiable.  No trades.  Cash only.  Buyer pays transfer fee.  Transfer must be done face to face with current FFL holder in Pittsburgh area.  I WILL NOT SHIP TO FFL.  I recommend using Guns of Our Fathers in Upper St. Clair as they will transfer for $25 and are open on Saturdays from 10-4.  However, since buyer pays, I will agree to use other FFL holders provided they are within reasonable driving distance of the North Hills, and have a website I can view beforehand.
